title: The Fifth Risk by Michael Lewis (.m4b)
description: The Fifth Risk by Michael Lewis Requirements: M4B Player, 146 MB, 62 kbps, 5 hrs 10 mins Overview: 'The election happened … And then there was radio silence.' The morning after Trump was elected president, the people who ran the US Department of Energy - an agency that deals with some of the most powerful risks facing humanity - waited to welcome the incoming administration's transition team. Nobody appeared. Across the US government, the same thing happened: nothing. People don't notice when stuff goes right. That is the stuff government does. It manages everything that underpins our lives from funding free school meals, to policing rogue nuclear activity, to predicting extreme weather events. It steps in where private investment fears to tread, innovates and creates knowledge, assesses extreme long-term risk. Genre: Audiobooks > Non-Fiction https://i.imgur.com/b5ckVTB.jpg
